<topic id="author-xhtml-doc-type">
  <title>XHTML Document Type (Framework)</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Predefined frameworks<indexterm>XHTML</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>XHTML document type</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>The Extensible HyperText Markup Language (XHTML), is a markup language that has the same
      depth of expression as HTML, but also conforms to XML syntax.</p>
    <section id="file_definition">
      <title>File Definition</title>
      <p>A file is considered to be an XHTML document when the root element name is
          <codeph>html</codeph>.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="default_document_templates">
      <title>Default Document Templates</title>
      <p>There are a variety of default <i>XHTML</i> templates available when creating <xref
          href="new-dialog-sa.dita#new-dialog-sa" product="author developer editor">new documents
          from templates</xref><xref href="creating-from-templates.dita#creating-from-templates"
          product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">new documents from
        templates</xref>, including <uicontrol>1.0 Strict</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>1.0
          Transitional</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>1.1 DTD Based</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>1.1 Schema
          Based</uicontrol>, and more.</p>
      <p>The default templates for XHTML documents are located in the <filepath><term
            conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
          />/frameworks/xhtml/templates/</filepath> folder. </p>
    </section>
    <section id="default_schema">
      <title>Default Schema</title>
      <p>Default schemas that are used if one is not detected in the XHTML file are stored in the
        following locations:<ul id="ul_ujs_2mf_fr">
          <li>XHTML 1.0 - <filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
              />/frameworks/xhtml/dtd/</filepath> or <filepath><term
                conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
            />/frameworks/xhtml/nvdl/</filepath>.</li>
          <li>XHTML 1.1 - <filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
              />/frameworks/xhtml11/dtd/</filepath> or <filepath><term
                conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
              />/frameworks/xhtml11/schema/</filepath>.</li>
          <li>XHTML 5 - <filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
              />/frameworks/xhtml/xhtml5 (epub3)/</filepath>.</li>
        </ul></p>
    </section>
    <section product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse" id="default_css">
      <title>Default CSS</title>
      <p>The default CSS files used for rendering XHTML content in <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol>
        mode are stored in <filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
          />/frameworks/xhtml/css/</filepath>.</p>
      <p>By default, these default CSS files are merged with any that are specified in the document.
        For more information, see <xref
          href="selecting-combining-multiple-css-styles.dita#selecting-combining-multiple-css-styles"
        />.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="default_xml_catalogs">
      <title>Default XML Catalogs</title>
      <p>The default <xref keyref="glossentry_xml-catalog"><term>XML Catalogs</term></xref> for the
        XHTML document type are as follows:<ul>
          <li><filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
              />/frameworks/xhtml/dtd/xhtmlcatalog.xml</filepath></li>
          <li><filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
              />/frameworks/relaxng/catalog.xml</filepath></li>
          <li><filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
              />/frameworks/nvdl/catalog.xml</filepath></li>
          <li><filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
              />/frameworks/xhtml11/dtd/xhtmlcatalog.xml</filepath></li>
          <li><filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"
              />/frameworks/xhtml11/schema/xhtmlcatalog.xml</filepath></li>
          <li><filepath><term conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"/>/xhtml5
              (epub3)/catalog-compat.xml</filepath></li>
        </ul></p>
    </section>
